quote: 'Dear Ms. Buffay. Thank you for calling attention to our error. We have credited your account with five hundred dollars. We're sorry for the inconvenience, and hope you'll accept this- (Searches in her purse) -football phone as our free gift.' Do you believe this?! Now I have a thousand dollars, and a football phone!

quote: What bank is this?

quote: Hi.

quote: C'mon!

author: Monica
quote: Really!

quote: You know what I like most about him, though?

author: All

author: All
quote: Yeah...

author: Ross
quote: Well..

quote: WE WON!! Thank you! Yes!

quote: Fantastic! I have one question: How is that possible?

quote: Alan.

quote: I mean, it-it was like, it was like he made us into a team.

author: Phoebe
quote: I know.

quote: Weird Girl, what are you doing?

quote: No, I want you to have it. I don't want it.

quote: No, no, I ha-I have to give you something.

quote: Oh, that's fine, no.

quote: No. 'Cause you need that. No, it's okay, thanks.

quote: Please, let me do something.

author: Lizzie
quote: Okay.

author: Phoebe
quote: Okay.

quote: Nooo!

quote: Oh, (Imitating Ross) "you do, do you"?

quote: Yeah, 'cause otherwise someone might get what they actually ordered.

author: Rachel
quote: Ohh-ho-hooohhh. The hair comes out, and the gloves come on.

quote: Hey, y'know, I have had it with you guys and your cancer and your emphysema and your heart disease. The bottom line is, smoking is cool, and you know it.

author: Rachel
quote: (holding the phone out to Chandler) Chandler? It's Alan, he wants to speak to you.

author: Chandler
quote: Really? He does? (taking the phone) Hey, buddy, what's up! Oh, she told you about that, huh. Well, yeah, I have one now and then. Well, yeah, now. Well, it's not that big- ..well, that's true,.. Gee, y'know, no-one- no-one's ever put it like that before. Well, okay, thanks! (He hands the phone back and stubs out his cigarette.)

quote: (to Ross, who has wandered up) God, he's good.

quote: Yeah.

quote: Ooh, Lambchop. How old is that sock? If I had a sock on my hand for thirty years it'd be talking too.

quote: (entering) Hey. Where's Joey?

quote: I think he's across the hall.

quote: (deadpan) Ooh, I'm alive with pleasure now.

quote: Does anyone want the rest of this Pop-Tart?

quote: Hey, I might!

quote: Uh, Joey..

So if that sounds like I'm okay, okay, then you can tell them I'm okay, okay?

quote: Hey, this- (she gives him a look and the guys back off) Heyy...

author: Rachel
quote: I'm so sorry, you guys. I didn't mean to bring you down.

author: Monica
quote: No, you were right. I don't have a plan. (There's a knock on the door.)

author: Pizza Guy
quote: (yelling from outside) Pizza guy!

author: Rachel
quote: Thank God. Food. (She goes to answer the door.)

author: Monica
quote: Phoebe?

author: Phoebe
quote: What?

author: Monica
quote: Do you have a plan?

author: Phoebe
quote: I don't even have a 'pl'.

author: Pizza Guy
quote: Hi, one, uh, mushroom, green pepper and onion?

author: Rachel
quote: (miserably) No, no, that's not what we ordered... We ordered a fat-free crust with extra cheese.

author: Pizza Guy
quote: Wait, you're not 'G.Stephanopoulos?' Man, my dad's gonna kill me!

author: Monica
quote: (leaping off of the couch and runs up) Wait! Did you say 'G.Stephanopoulos?'

author: Pizza Guy
quote: Yeah. This one goes across the street, I must have given him yours. Oh, bonehead, bonehead!

author: Monica
quote: Wait, was this a-a small mediterranean guy with curiously intelligent good looks?

author: Pizza Guy
quote: Yeah, that sounds about right.

author: Monica
quote: Was he wearing a stunning blue suit?

author: Phoebe
quote: And-and a power tie?

author: Pizza Guy
quote: No, pretty much just a towel.

author: Monica
quote: (staggered) Oh God.

author: Pizza Guy
quote: So you guys want me to take this back?

author: Monica
quote: Are you nuts?! We've got George Stephanopoulos' pizza! (Rachel pays him, Monica grabs some binoculars, and runs to the window.)

author: Rachel
quote: Uh, Pheebs? Who's George Snuffalopagus?

author: Phoebe
quote: Big Bird's friend.

author: Monica
quote: I see pizza!

author: Phoebe
quote: Oh, I wanna see! Lemme see! Lemme see! (She runs up and takes the binoculars.)

author: Rachel
quote: Hello? Who are we spying on?

author: Monica
quote: White House adviser? Clinton's campaign guy? The one with the great hair, sexy smile, really cute butt?

author: Rachel
quote: Oh, him, the little guy? Oh, I love him!

author: Phoebe
quote: Ooh, wait.. wait, I see a woman.

author: Monica
quote: Please tell me it's his mother.

author: Phoebe
quote: Definitely not his mother.

author: Monica
quote: Oh, no...

author: Phoebe
quote: Oh, wait, she's walking across the floor.. she's walking.. she's walking.. she's going for the pizza- (Yelling) Hey, that's not for you, bitch! (Phoebe covers her mouth with her hand walks away from the window.)

author: Chandler
quote: Excuse me, look, we've been here for over an hour, and a lot of people less sick than my friend have gone in. I mean, that guy with the toe thing? Who's he sleeping with? (She slides the gladd panel over and Chandler talks through it in a loud voice.) Oh, c'mon Dora, don't be mad... I know we both said some things we didn't mean, but that doesn't mean we still don't love each other. (To the waiting room.) Y'know, I feel like I've lost her.. (She slides the panel back, he turns, and it takes him by surprise.) Ba-!

author: Monica
quote: Light still out?

author: Rachel
quote: Yeah.

author: Monica
quote: Oh. Maybe they're- napping.

author: Rachel
quote: Oh please, they're having sex.

author: Monica and Phoebe
quote: Shut up!

author: Rachel
quote: So, whaddya think George is like?

author: Monica
quote: I think he's shy.

author: Phoebe
quote: Yeah?

author: Monica
quote: Yeah. I think you have to draw him out. And then- when you do- he's a preppy animal.

author: Ross
quote: I remember the moonlight coming through the window- and her face had the most incredible glow.

author: Chandler
quote: Yes, the moon, the glow, the magical feeling, you did this part- Could I get some painkillers over here, please?

author: Joey
quote: He's right, enough, already. What is the big deal about today? So you slept with her for the first time, so what? You slept with her for seven years after that.

author: Ross
quote: Look, it's just a little more complicated...

author: Chandler
quote: Well, what? What? What is it? That she left you? That she likes women? That she left you for another woman that likes women?

author: Ross
quote: Little louder, okay, I think there's a man on the twelfth floor in a coma that didn't quite hear you...

author: Chandler
quote: Then what?

author: Ross
quote: My first time with Carol was... (He mumbles the last part)

author: Joey
quote: What?

author: Ross
quote: It was my first time.

author: Joey
quote: With Carol? (Ross gives him a look.) Oh.

author: Chandler
quote: So in your whole life, you've only been with one(He gets a look too)oh.
